headlines.description: — Tobias Harris had 24 points and 10 rebounds as the Detroit Pistons held off the Charlotte Hornets 98-94 on Friday night for their fifth win in six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tobias Harris scores 24 points and Pistons hold off Hornets 98-94

headlines.description: — Tristan da Silva scored a career-high 25 points and the Orlando Magic overcame the loss of guard Jalen Suggs to back spasms to beat the struggling Toronto Raptors 106-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Da Silva scores career-high 25 points, Magic overcome loss of Suggs to beat Raptors 106-97

headlines.description: — Derrick White had 23 points and Jayson Tatum and Payton Pritchard added 20 each to lead the Boston Celtics to a 109-86 victory over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Derrick White scores 23 points as Celtics roll to 109-86 win over Rockets

events.name: Washington Wizards at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum highlighted a career high-tying 50 points with 10 3-pointers, and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped an 11-game losing streak with a 132-120 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum's 50 points helps the Pelicans snap an 11-game skid with a 132-120 win over the Wizards

events.name: New York Knicks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied in the fourth quarter to win their 14th straight game, 117-107 over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33 as Thunder rally past Knicks 117-107 for 14th straight win

headlines.description: — Evan Mobley had 34 points and 10 rebounds as the Cleveland Cavaliers ran their winning streak to nine games by beating the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 134-122 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Evan Mobley scores 34 as Cavaliers beat short-handed Mavericks 134-122, run win streak to 9 games

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama stole Nikola Jokic’s pass with 4 seconds left, and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the Denver Nuggets 113-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama denies Jokic in closing seconds as Spurs beat Nuggets 113-110

headlines.description: — Malik Monk scored 31 points, DeMar DeRozan added 29 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Memphis Grizzlies 138-130 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Monk scores 31 points in the Sacramento Kings 138-133 win over the Grizzlies

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 30 points to become the NBA's career leader in 30-point games, surpassing Michael Jordan's record during the Los Angeles Lakers' 119-102 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James breaks Jordan's record for 30-point games in Lakers' 119-102 win over Hawks
